title: ICE on nightly

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code `cargo new ice-repro && cd ice-repro` ```toml [package] name = "ice-repro" version = "0.1.0" edition = "2021" # See more keys and their definitions at https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/reference/manifest.html [dependencies] axum = "0.5.12" sea-orm = { version = "0.9.0", features = ["sqlx-postgres", "runtime-tokio-rustls", "macros"] } tokio = { version = "1.20.0", features = ["full"] } dotenv = "0.15.0" tracing-subscriber = "0.3.14" anyhow = "1.0.58" tower = "0.4.13" ethers = "0.14.0" tracing = "0.1.35" erc-nft-metadata = { version = "0.1.0", features = ["serde"] } ``` `cargo +nightly check` ### Meta This does **not** ICE on stable nor beta. `rustc --version --verbose` ``` rustc 1.62.0 (a8314ef7d 2022-06-27) binary: rustc commit-hash:
